                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                <head>No. 743.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bliss</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 24, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President desires the examination mentioned in my letter of yesterday to be
                    attended on the part of the Government, and the facts of the case to be fairly
                    and fully ascertained. He wishes no delay interposed; but if you think it
                    necessary for the full ascertainment of the facts, you will continue or adjourn
                    the examination.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
